Description: Provides an R interface to the FastKernelSurvivalSVM model from the 
    Python 'scikit-survival' package. The package enables fitting Survival Support 
    Vector Machines for right-censored outcomes using kernel methods. Users may 
    employ native kernels from 'scikit-learn' or define custom kernel functions 
    directly in R. Computation is delegated to the Python implementation via 
    'reticulate', while the package exposes a clean R API for fitting, predicting, 
    evaluating and summarizing survival SVM models.
Depends:
    R (>= 4.2.0)
Imports:
    reticulate
